<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a062376-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6305"><num value="6305">§ 6305.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the Fund $5,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2025 through 2029.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a062377-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/411/s6">Pub. L. 106–411, § 6</ref>, <date date="2000-11-01">Nov. 1, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1794">114 Stat. 1794</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/363/tVII/s703">Pub. L. 109–363, title VII, § 703</ref>, <date date="2006-10-17">Oct. 17, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/2082">120 Stat. 2082</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/116/9/tVII/s7001/c/2/D">Pub. L. 116–9, title VII, § 7001(c)(2)(D)</ref>, <date date="2019-03-12">Mar. 12, 2019</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/133/785">133 Stat. 785</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/118/159/dE/tLIII/s5306/b">Pub. L. 118–159, div. E, title LIII, § 5306(b)</ref>, <date date="2024-12-23">Dec. 23, 2024</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/138/2446">138 Stat. 2446</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
